      "id": "c251ddd1_aa5a16ed",
      "file_path": "jjb/global-templates-docker.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 846,
      "message": "To use the global-jjb docker jobs, you will need to not call this template  '{project-name}-{arch_tag}-{stream}-docker-version-java-daily'\nBut rather call:\n\"{project-name}-maven-docker-stage-{stream}\" which is the new equivalent. \nProject-name will need to be defined as \"policy-amd64\" or \"policy-arm64\" depending on the arch. \nIf you have the changes in jjb/policy files I can help you define review those",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 481,
        "name": "Jessica Wagantall",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jwagantall@linuxfoundation.org",
        "username": "jwagantall"
      },
      "updated": "2019-08-05 20:56:11.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dc134fc8_084401b9",
      "file_path": "jjb/global-templates-docker.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 846,
      "message": "Renaming the project name to \"policy-amd64\" or \"policy-arm64\" means changing it for the master job and manifest too. This results in duplicating them as well, and we don't want that. Only the build jobs should be duplicated. Can we call \"{project-name}-maven-docker-stage-{stream}\" with a different value for project-name? Something like {project-name-arch}-maven-docker-stage-{stream}?",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5109,
        "name": "Cristina Pauna",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "cristina.pauna@enea.com",
        "username": "cristinapauna"
